# Offline First

LexMastery is designed to function even when internet connectivity is poor or unavailable.

Offline capability is a product requirement, not an enhancement.

---

# Philosophy

The application should remain useful without an internet connection.

Users should be able to:

- Read downloaded lessons
- Review flashcards
- Access bookmarks
- View cached progress
- Continue quizzes where possible

Connectivity should enhance the experience, not enable it.

---

# Data Priority

Every feature must define its data strategy.

Example:

Static Content
→ Cache aggressively

User Profile
→ Cache and synchronize

Quiz Results
→ Queue if offline

Authentication
→ Secure storage only

AI Chat
→ Online only

---

# Cache Strategy

Prefer:

Cache First

↓

Background Refresh

↓

Update UI

Avoid unnecessary network requests.

---

# Synchronization

When connectivity returns:

- Sync pending mutations
- Refresh stale content
- Resolve conflicts
- Notify users only when necessary

Synchronization must occur in the background.

---

# Offline Queue

Mutations created while offline should be queued.

Examples:

Bookmarks

Study Progress

Lesson Completion

Quiz Submission

Notes

Retry automatically.

---

# Connectivity

Monitor network status globally.

Controllers should react to connectivity changes.

Avoid repeated polling.

---

# Conflict Resolution

Server is the source of truth.

When conflicts occur:

- Merge where possible
- Preserve user-generated content
- Never silently discard user work

---

# Expiration

Cached data should include metadata.

Example:

- createdAt
- updatedAt
- expiresAt

Repositories decide when data becomes stale.

---

# UI Indicators

Clearly communicate offline state.

Examples:

Offline banner

Syncing indicator

Cached badge

Never block reading cached content.

---

# Testing

Test:

- Offline launch
- Reconnection
- Queue replay
- Cache expiration
- Conflict resolution

---

# Cursor Instructions

Every new feature must define:

- Cache strategy
- Sync strategy
- Offline behavior
- Expiration policy